# Bug Prevention Checklist

Apply these before finishing any change:

## Multi-tenancy
- Every query filters by `organizationId` from JWT — never from request body
- Use `*Access.Get*Async(db, id, organizationId)` helpers for entity lookup
- Return `NotFoundException` (not 403) when resource is outside org scope

## Async & EF
- Use `async`/`await` end-to-end; pass `CancellationToken` to all handlers
- Avoid multiple `SaveChangesAsync` on the same entity graph unless state is clear
- Include required navigations (`Provider.Credential`, `Endpoints`) before operations that need them

## API contracts
- Request DTOs in `PodPilot.Contracts`; map to commands in controllers
- Never leak `EncryptedApiKey`, raw tokens, or provider API responses
- Return consistent `ApiResponse<T>` shape for all endpoints

## Frontend
- Sync `PERMISSIONS` and `ROLE_PERMISSIONS` when adding backend permissions
- Invalidate React Query caches after mutations; include org id in query keys
- Handle 401/403 from API with user-visible messages

## Before marking done
- Run `dotnet build` (warnings are errors)
- Run `dotnet test`
- Run `npm run build` when touching `web/`
- Apply EF migrations for schema changes

## When correcting the AI repeatedly
Add the fix as a rule in `.cursor/rules/` so it persists for the team.
